1. We know that in the diagram, point \( P \) is a common vertex for angles \( \angle PQR \) and \( \angle PMN \).
2. Since \( PMN \) is a straight line, the angle opposite \( \angle PQR \) on the straight line \( PMN \) is \( 180^\circ - \angle PQR \).
3. Since \( \angle PQR = 48^\circ \), the angle on the straight line opposite to it is \( 180^\circ - 48^\circ = 132^\circ \).
4. Because \( PMN \) is a straight line, the sum of the angles around point \( P \) is \( 180^\circ \). So, the angle \( \angle PMN \) is the same as the angle on the straight line opposite \( \angle PQR \).

Thus, the measure of \( \angle PMN \) is \( 132^\circ \).

